  "id": "phekb-sleep-apnea-dx",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "sleep-apnea",
  "name": "Sleep Apnea - Diagnosis Code Query (OSA + CSA)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find sleep apnea patients via diagnosis codes. Sleep apnea is documented under multiple SNOMED codes by mechanism (obstructive vs central) and severity (mild/moderate/severe OSA). Synthea distributes patients across the parent sleep apnea code, OSA syndrome, central sleep apnea, OSA of adult, mixed sleep apnea, and severity-specific OSA codes.",
  "prompt": "Find all patients diagnosed with sleep apnea, including obstructive sleep apnea, central sleep apnea, and mixed sleep apnea — across all severity levels.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all patients with sleep apnea.",
    "broad": "Find all patients diagnosed with any form of sleep apnea — obstructive sleep apnea (OSA), central sleep apnea (CSA), mixed sleep apnea, and OSA in adults across all severity levels (mild, moderate, severe).",
    "expert": "I need to identify all sleep apnea patients. Sleep apnea is documented under multiple SNOMED codes from the HL7 Sleep Apnea Disorders value set (OID 2.16.840.1.113762.1.4.1222.102): Sleep apnea (73430006) is the parent concept, with mechanism-specific Obstructive sleep apnea syndrome (78275009), Central sleep apnea syndrome (27405005), Obstructive sleep apnea of adult (1101000119103), and Mixed sleep apnea (230493001). Search Condition resources for all five codes."
  },
